articles.description: Freshman Jacob Epperson scored a season-high 15 points and Marcus Foster added 12 points and eight rebounds to help Creighton beat Division II Bemidji State 94-46 on Tuesday night.
articles.headline: After slow start, Creighton overpowers D-II Bemidji State

articles.description: Hunter Rhodes had 12 points and Bennett Koch added 10 as Northern Iowa held Evansville scoreless in the final two minutes to secure a 47-41 win on Tuesday night.
articles.headline: Northern Iowa wins it at FT line, beating Evansville 47-41

articles.description: Jared Terrell had 17 points and 16th-ranked Rhode Island extended its winning streak to 16 games with an 85-67 victory over Richmond on Tuesday night.
articles.headline: No. 16 URI streak reaches 16 with 85-67 win over Richmond

images.caption: Jared Terrell gets the lob from Jeff Dowtin and slams it home with two hands for the Rams.
images.name: URI's Terrell climbs ladder for alley-oop

articles.description: Donta Hall receives a lob  from half court and tips in the basket with a defender all over him.
articles.headline: Alabama's Hall cant not be stopped

images.caption: Donta Hall receives a lob  from half court and tips in the basket with a defender all over him.
images.name: Donta Hall receives a lob  from half court and tips in the basket with a defender all over him.

articles.description: Kevin McKay came off the bench to score a career-high 33 points and hit several big shots down the stretch to help Central Michigan pull away late for an 80-72 victory over Northern Illinois on Tuesday night.
articles.headline: McKay sparks Central Michigan past Northern Illinois 80-72

articles.description: The Tigers notch their longest SEC win streak in team history with an upset win against the Aggies.
articles.headline: Missouri holds on to beat No. 21 Texas A&M 62-58

images.caption: The Tigers notch their longest SEC win streak in team history with an upset win against the Aggies.

videos.description: Virginia Tech's Nickeil Alexander-Walker swings the pass to Justin Bibbs behind the arc for the 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Alexander-Walker finds Bibbs for 3

videos.description: After grabbing the offensive rebound, Kentucky's Quade Green lobs a pass up to Nick Richards for the alley-oop slam.
videos.headline: Green sets up Richards on the oop

videos.description: Virginia Tech's Ahmed Hill nails the contested layup to earn a chance at a 3-point play.
videos.headline: Hill sinks contested layup for 3-point chance

videos.description: Kentucky's PJ Washington finds Shai Gilgeous-Alexander down low for the layup in the first half.
videos.headline: Diallo's steal sets up Gilgeous-Alexander layup

videos.description: Kentucky's PJ Washington finds Quade Green behind the arc for the contested 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Green buries contested 3

videos.description: After grabbing the defensive rebound, Virginia Tech's Chris Clarke goes coast-to-coast and converts a contested layup for an and-1 opportunity.
videos.headline: Clarke nails tough layup for and-1 chance

videos.description: Kentucky's Kevin Knox swings the ball up top to Hamidou Diallo for the 3-pointer in the first half.
videos.headline: Knox finds Diallo open downtown for the 3

videos.description: Kentucky's Quade Green takes it down the lane and sinks the floater in the first half.
videos.headline: Green converts tough floater

videos.description: Virginia Tech's Kerry Blackshear Jr. gets the ball in the post and spins by Wenyen Gabriel for the layup.
videos.headline: Blackshear spins by Gabriel for the layup

videos.description: Kentucky's Quade Green fires a long pass to Kevin Knox setting up the tough layup and 3-point chance.
videos.headline: Knox drives to the rack for and-1 opportunity

videos.description: Following the turnover from Virginia Tech's Nickeil Alexander-Walker, Kentucky's Hamidou Diallo lobs a pass up to PJ Washington for the alley-oop finish.
videos.headline: Diallo connects with Washington for the oop

videos.description: Kentucky's PJ Washington swings the ball over to Hamidou Diallo for the 3-pointer in the second half.
videos.headline: Washington finds Diallo for the 3

videos.description: Late in the second half, Kentucky's Quade Green sets up Hamidou Diallo in the corner for the big 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Diallo knocks down clutch 3-pointer

videos.description: The Wildcats put on a show at the 3-point line and claim a victory over the Hokies to improve to 8-1.
videos.headline: No. 8 Kentucky tops Virginia Tech 93-86

tracking.trackingName: SEC_NCB Highlight (Kentucky tops V Tech) 171216 ESHEET

videos.description: Dick Vitale and Dan Shulman highlight Kentucky's terrific 3-point shooting in the 93-86 win over Virginia Tech.
videos.headline: Vitale, Shulman credit 3-point shooting in Wildcats win

videos.description: Hamidou Diallo scores 20 points in No. 8 Kentucky's 96-83 victory over Virginia Tech.
videos.headline: Kentucky tops Virginia Tech for 7th straight win

videos.description: Kentucky's head coach John Calipari talks about his players having their own special characteristics that set them apart.
videos.headline: Wildcats creating own identity
